Littermate syndrome is real and it is harsh. Two males typically start fighting loads- even if they aren’t siblings, two intact males usually won’t mix since there are so many hormones and so much dominance. Even if the fighting didn’t happen the other part of littermate syndrome would be them getting overly attached to one another and never being able to be separated. Two males typically start fighting loads- even if they aren’t siblings, two intact males usually won’t mix since there are so many hormones and so much dominance.
